definition: to obey/to follow/to arrange/to make reasonable/along/favorable

sentences.english: But the lottery of friendship could even depend on who we happen to meet first.
sentences.chinese: 但這種緣分甚至可能還取決於相識的先後順序。

sentences.english: You know the right order, and if you do it in batches it saves time.
sentences.chinese: 你知道做事的先後順序，分批次操作會節省時間。

sentences.english: Start by thinking about what are the sequences.
sentences.chinese: 啓動的時候應該考慮下先後順序。

sentences.english: What do you put next to what?
SNS does not guarantee messages will be received in the exact order they were published.
sentences.chinese: SNS不能保證按照發布消息的先後順序接收消息。

sentences.english: 2a Listen and number the sentences in the order you hear them in activity 1a.
sentences.chinese: 聽一遍，按你在1a中聽到的先後順序給句子編號。

sentences.english: The items on this list are in no particular order.
sentences.chinese: 如下目錄分類並無特別的先後順序。

sentences.english: These operations are receive activities that run in sequential order.
sentences.chinese: 這些操作是按先後順序運行的接收活動。

sentences.english: That which team shall be first kick-off in football match is determined by coin toss.
sentences.chinese: 足球比賽通過投硬幣來決定發球的先後順序。

sentences.english: Indexed file organization stores records in sequential order.
sentences.chinese: 索引文件組織按照先後順序儲存記錄。

sentences.english: 1b Listen and number the pictures above in the order you hear them.
sentences.chinese: 聽一遍錄音，按你聽到的先後順序給上面的圖畫編號。

sentences.english: The options are not ordered so you can specified in any sequence.
sentences.chinese: 這些選項不分先後順序，所以您可以以任意次序指定。

to read and pass on/to pass on for perusal
to do sth in place of sb else
